              }
            ],
            "text": "creaming method"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the foundation. How long you cream the butter and sugar directly affects how much the cake rises. Three minutes of proper creaming produces a noticeably lighter crumb than one minute of desultory mixing. The cocoa replaces flour in the ratio 1:1 by weight; the total dry weight stays the same as a standard Victoria sponge."
          }
